    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1869-07-01T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1869-07-01T00:00:00-05:00" n="402" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d402">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Willey</persName>,
                                    district attorney, to Mr. <persName type="to">Field</persName>,
                                    Assistant Attorney-General.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <dateline>
                    <placeName>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">New London,
                                    Connecticut</hi>
                    </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1869-07-01">
                        <hi rend="italic">July</hi> 1,
                                1869</date>.</dateline>
                <p rend="flushleft">
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">W. A. Field</hi>,<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">Assistant Attorney-General, Washington:</hi>
                </p>
                <p>Your telegram is received. I have telegraphed the marshal at New
                                Haven to proceed at once to Milford, to hold the schooners Fancy and
                                Winona, their arms, ammunition, and men, in custody till further
                                orders. The enlistment of men was in the southern district of New
                                York, and should be presented in that district.</p>
                <p>
                    <seg type="margin">[85]</seg> Is it the purpose of the Government to
                                libel *the vessel and cargo as forfeited? If so, instruct me to do
                                so.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>HIRAM WILLEY,<lb/>
                        <hi rend="italic">United States
                                        Attorney.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
